[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    45[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThe risk profile is comparable to Recipe 3.7 in clinical-safety consequence terms (the post-discharge program contributes to bedside clinical decision-making through care-manager outreach and same-day clinic add-ons; missed alerts produce missed deteriorations and missed readmission-prevention opportunities) but distinct in temporal-cadence terms (daily-cadence rather than per-event-cadence), in workflow-integration terms (care management staff outreach rather than rapid response team page), in equity-stakes terms (digital-engagement bias amplification produces population-level harms that map onto socioeconomic disparities in ways the in-hospital deterioration system does not), and in reimbursement-and-billing terms (RPM CPT codes 99453, 99454, 99457, 99458 produce billable-activity capture requirements that Recipe 3.7 does not have). The recipe correctly addresses the elevated risk in the Equity-Is-A-Deployment-Design-Problem-Not-A-Model-Problem framing, the Causal-Inference-Is-The-Biggest-Research-To-Production-Gap framing, the Documentation-And-Reimbursement framing in Why This Isn't Production-Ready, and the Decommissioning-Criteria framing.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    46[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    47[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThe Honest Take and the Why This Isn't Production-Ready section together are publication-ready voice; the "Why Anomaly Detection Instead of Just Predict Readmission" subsection and the "The Operational Anatomy of a Post-Discharge Episode" subsection are the recipe's biggest pedagogical contributions. The MEDIUM-finding cluster is an evenly distributed mix of architectural-completeness gaps (A1 idempotency, A2 DLQs, A3 cold-start operational mitigation, A4 treatment-effect-on-prediction handling, A5 engagement-decay routing, A6 reference-data versioning, A7 multi-cohort architecture) and PHI/governance backstops (S1 worklist payload PHI, S2 subgroup governance). These are the right next-pass priorities; with them addressed, Recipe 3.8 sits at the same publication-ready quality bar as Recipe 3.7 and the strongest Chapter 2 recipes.[K
