[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    134[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mBut the BAA-discipline forward reference that Chapter 2's recipes (especially 2.4-2.10) settled is missing. Bedrock with Amazon Titan (or Amazon Nova) foundation models is HIPAA-eligible under the BAA; third-party models on Bedrock (Anthropic Claude, Meta Llama, Cohere, AI21, Mistral) have differing BAA postures and the model's terms of service must be reviewed before PHI-bearing prompts are sent. The recipe's "HIPAA-eligible Bedrock foundation models" phrasing in the TODO doesn't differentiate.[K
