[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    136[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mAlso missing: minimum-necessary prompt construction discipline (the recipe's Step 6 [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mbuild_outreach_explanation_prompt[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m carries [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcohort[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdays_post_discharge[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcomposite_tier[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mtop_drivers[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mper_modality_scores[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mengagement_status[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mrecent_interventions[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m; the recent_interventions list is unspecified but a naive implementation would carry the full intervention free-text including care-manager notes); output filtering for clinical-recommendation hallucinations (an LLM that says "increase the diuretic dose to 80 mg" instead of "consider diuretic titration per standing orders" produces evidentiary problems for the FDA CDS exemption posture); and a full prompt-and-response audit trail tied to the worklist row ID. Same finding shape as Recipes 3.3 V2, 3.4 S4, 3.5 S5, 3.6 S7, 3.7 S5.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    137[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Expand the Bedrock paragraph: "Bedrock with Amazon foundation models (Titan, Nova) is HIPAA-eligible under the BAA; third-party models on Bedrock (Anthropic Claude, Meta Llama, others) have differing BAA postures, and the model's terms of service must be reviewed before PHI-bearing prompts are sent. Construct prompts with minimum-necessary context (the cohort, the post-discharge day, the top SHAP-driven feature names and values, the calibrated probability tier, the engagement summary, the de-identified summary of recent interventions; not the full intervention free-text or the full chart). Filter outputs for clinical-recommendation language: the LLM should produce evaluation-suggestion language ('consider diuretic titration per standing orders') rather than treatment-decision language ('increase furosemide to 80 mg'). Filter outputs for non-recommendation framing ('weight has trended up over 3 days' is acceptable; 'patient is decompensating' is not without explicit human verification). Log every prompt and response to the audit trail tied to the worklist row ID; the prompt-response pair is part of the evidence-of-decision under the FDA CDS exemption (the care manager must be able to see the reasoning that underlies the suggestion). See Chapter 2's generative AI recipes for the established BAA discipline."[K
