[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    181[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The architecture is event-driven from the EHR, HIE, and claims feeds for outcome events (readmissions to your hospital and to other facilities, ED visits, post-discharge mortality, observation stays, program graduations) and from the care management UI for intervention events (outreach attempted, contact made, intervention delivered, escalations made). EventBridge guarantees at-least-once delivery; Lambda asynchronous invocation also retries on failure. If EventBridge redelivers an outcome event, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mon_outcome_event[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m runs twice on the same outcome. Each run:[K
