[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    271[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "The Problem" causality-and-correlation paragraph ("A patient whose weight went up and got readmitted shows the model that weight gain predicts readmission. A patient whose weight went up, got a phone call, got a same-day diuretic adjustment, and didn't get readmitted shows the model that weight gain doesn't predict readmission. The intervention itself disrupts the prediction problem. This is the fundamental 'treatment effect on prediction' issue, and naive supervised learning on observational data produces models that quietly absorb the historical intervention pattern. You end up predicting 'patient who would have been readmitted in the absence of an intervention' using a model that was trained on a world where interventions happened"); "The Technology" Causal-Inference-Aware-Models subsection ("a growing body of work tries to handle the treatment-effect-on-prediction problem by modeling the intervention explicitly: counterfactual estimators, target-trial-emulation, instrumental variables, propensity-matched controls. These are research-grade as of 2026; most production deployments accept the bias and validate prospectively"); The Honest Take's "Causal inference is the biggest research-to-production gap" lesson with the explicit recommendation to run randomized rollouts when feasible; Step 4 [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcompute_features[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and Step 5 [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mscore_patient[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m (no architectural primitive shows how to handle the treatment-effect bias).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    272[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly identifies the treatment-effect-on-prediction problem as a fundamental modeling concern and correctly names the cleanest architectural mitigation (randomized rollout for causal evaluation; matched-cohort or target-trial-emulation as the next-best). The Honest Take is explicit: "If your program supports it, run a randomized rollout: half the eligible patients get the program, half get usual care."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    273[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    274[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mBut the pseudocode does not show how to operationalize a randomized rollout or a matched-cohort evaluation. There is no architectural primitive for:[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    275[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Random assignment of newly-discharged patients to "program" vs "usual care" tracks at enrollment time, with the assignment captured in the patient-state record and propagated through the worklist construction (program-track patients appear on the worklist; usual-care-track patients are excluded from the worklist but their outcomes are still captured for the comparison).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    276[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Matched-cohort construction at evaluation time (propensity-matching usual-care-track patients to program-track patients on baseline characteristics and discharge-time risk score).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    277[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Target-trial-emulation framing where the eligibility criteria, treatment assignment, and follow-up rules are documented and adhered to throughout the cohort identification.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    278[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Causal-inference-aware feature engineering (excluding intervention-derived features when training the model that predicts "patient who would have been readmitted in the absence of intervention").[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    279[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    280[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mA reader who treats the pseudocode as the implementation specification produces a system that does observational supervised learning on a population where interventions and outcomes are entangled, which the prose explicitly identifies as producing biased models.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    281[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    282[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThis is calibrated against very high prose emphasis: the Honest Take says "the cleanest evidence for program effectiveness comes from randomized trials" and "If randomization isn't feasible, target-trial-emulation with propensity matching is the next best thing." A reader implementing from the pseudocode does not produce either pattern.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    283[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add a paragraph to the General Architecture Pattern's "Scoring Service" or "Outcome Capture" subsection naming the randomized-rollout primitive as a first-class architectural concern: "For program-effectiveness evaluation, the architecture should support randomized assignment of newly-discharged patients to 'program' vs 'usual care' tracks at enrollment time. The patient-state record carries an [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mevaluation_track[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m attribute set at enrollment (random assignment with a stratification by discharge-time risk score and condition cohort to ensure balance). The worklist construction excludes usual-care-track patients but the outcome-capture path tracks both tracks. The label-assembly path linked to the training-labels S3 partition stratifies labels by track for both retraining and effectiveness evaluation. When randomization isn't feasible, the architecture supports target-trial-emulation: documented eligibility criteria, documented treatment-assignment rules (intervention or no intervention), and documented follow-up windows; the training-labels archive captures the criteria, assignments, and outcomes in structured form for propensity-matched analysis at evaluation time."[K
