[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    448[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add a HIE/claims-feed-security paragraph to the Why-These-Services EHR-feed paragraph: "HIE feeds typically arrive via HL7 v2 over MLLPS, FHIR R4 subscriptions over HTTPS with mutual TLS or SMART-on-FHIR OAuth, C-CDA/CCD over Direct Trust, or bulk FHIR export from regional HIE clearinghouses. Claims feeds typically arrive via EDI 837 transactions over SFTP from the clearinghouse, EDI 835 remittance advice for outcome timing, or near-real-time claims APIs from ACO/value-based-care platforms. Each path has different security posture and network requirements; the integration plan should treat HIE and claims as separate dependencies from the primary EHR feed, each with its own trading-partner agreement, BAA-or-equivalent, and audit trail. AWS Transfer Family supports SFTP-based clearinghouse feeds with KMS-encrypted S3 destination; AWS Direct Connect supports HIE-side gateway bridging; API Gateway with mutual TLS supports FHIR R4 subscription endpoints."[K
