[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    497[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mBut two specific numbers warrant additional caveat regardless of whether the table is replaced: the AUROC ranges across configurations (0.62-0.81) imply head-to-head measurements that vary substantially by population (academic medical center vs community hospital), outcome definition (all-cause-30-day vs condition-specific vs composite), monitoring program design (low-touch vs high-touch), and data availability (RPM-rich vs PRO-only). The PRAUC ranges are particularly population-dependent because the readmission base rate varies substantially across hospitals.[K
