[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    527[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Expected Results sample worklist row [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mnarrative[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m field ("Suggested outreach: confirm the weight trend, ask about dyspnea on exertion and orthopnea, ask about diuretic adherence and any recent changes (skipped doses, side effects), ask about diet over the weekend, and consider a same-day add-on with the cardiology transitions clinic or a diuretic adjustment per standing orders.").[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    528[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The sample narrative is well-constructed and demonstrates the constraint boundary the recipe correctly establishes ("constrained: cite features, suggest outreach focus, never prescribe treatment"). The narrative cites features ("weight has trended up about 1 lb per day over the last 3 days (198 to 204; cumulative 6 lbs above the discharge dry weight)"), suggests outreach steps ("confirm the weight trend, ask about dyspnea on exertion and orthopnea, ask about diuretic adherence ... ask about diet"), and includes the closing constraint via the suggested_outreach [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mescalation_to_provider[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m field ("Suggest provider review if weight trajectory continues despite intervention or if patient reports dyspnea at rest"). This is largely the right model output discipline.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    529[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    530[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mBut one phrase ("a diuretic adjustment per standing orders") sits at the boundary between "suggest outreach focus" and "prescribe treatment." Standing-order diuretic titration is a specific clinical action; framing it as a "consideration" in a narrative is acceptable for the FDA-CDS-exemption posture (transparent reasoning, supports rather than replaces clinician judgment), but a more conservative phrasing would land further from the boundary. Some hospital clinical-governance committees would push back on this specific phrasing on the grounds that "a diuretic adjustment per standing orders" approaches "increase the diuretic now."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    531[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    532[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe recipe correctly identifies this concern in the Bedrock paragraph framing and in the closed-loop discussion ("Standing orders for medication titration ... can work in narrow scenarios with strong governance, but they raise the regulatory bar substantially"), but the sample narrative includes a near-treatment-recommendation. A reader implementing the explanation layer who uses the sample as a template will produce narratives that drift toward treatment recommendations rather than outreach-focus suggestions.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    533[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    534[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mSame shape as Recipe 3.7 V4 ("consideration of empiric antibiotic timing per local sepsis protocol").[K
