[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    561[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPattern: A2 (DLQ / poison-message handling) is operationally critical for Recipe 3.8 specifically because the system feeds care-management decisions and RPM CPT code billing documentation.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m A dropped event in the device-ingest path is a missed RPM measurement; a dropped event in the event-normalizer path is a missed engagement signal that looks operationally identical to patient disengagement; a dropped event in the outcome-capture path is a missed positive-class label. For the FDA-CDS-exemption posture and the RPM CPT code billing posture, silently-dropped events are documentation gaps. The DLQ-depth alarm threshold for the device-ingest, event-normalizer, and outcome-capture paths should be 1 (single-event sensitivity).[K
