[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    603[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThe combined picture from the code review's three WARNINGs and this expert review's eight MEDIUM findings is that Recipe 3.8 has the most prose-vs-pseudocode-vs-Python asymmetries of any chapter-3 recipe to date. The prose is the strongest in the chapter on operational discipline (cold-start uniform high-touch, randomized rollouts, engagement-decay as first-class signal, multi-cohort architecture, RPM CPT code billing documentation, equity as deployment-design); the pseudocode does not architecturally enforce these disciplines; and the Python implementation has three distinct silent-failure correctness bugs (active-enrollment lookup, GSI pagination, top-drivers standardization). The editorial work is to close the prose-vs-pseudocode gap (A3, A4, A5, A6, A7) without losing the prose's operational authority, and to ensure the Python companion's correctness gaps don't propagate into reader implementations.[K
