[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    710[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThere are zero HIGH findings. The MEDIUM findings cluster heavily on prose-vs-pseudocode asymmetry: A3 (cold-start uniform-high-touch), A4 (randomized rollout), A5 (engagement-decay first-class signal), A7 (multi-cohort architecture) are all places where the prose makes a discipline claim that the canonical pseudocode walkthrough doesn't reflect. This is the most pronounced prose-vs-pseudocode-asymmetry signature of any chapter-3 recipe to date and reflects the recipe's substantive engagement with operational realities. A6 (reference-data versioning propagation) is the same recurring pattern as Recipes 3.5, 3.6, 3.7. A1 (idempotency) and A2 (DLQs) are the recurring chapter-wide patterns. S1 (worklist payload PHI minimization) is the latest variant of the recurring chapter pattern. S2 (subgroup governance) is the seven-recipe chapter-wide pattern.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    711[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    712[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe three highest-leverage fixes are A3 (cold-start uniform-high-touch), A5 (engagement-decay first-class pathway), and A4 (randomized rollout primitive). All three are explicitly emphasized in The Honest Take and all three are not architecturally enforced in the pseudocode. A3 and A5 are the most-consequential teaching gaps because they affect daily operational reality (cold-start patients in the highest-risk window; previously-engaged patients who stop engaging). A4 is the highest-stakes evaluation discipline (randomized rollouts produce defensible evidence for executive review and protect the program from "we don't know if it's working" challenges).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    713[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    714[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding A1 is the now-recurring trigger-idempotency pattern, surfacing for the thirteenth consecutive recipe (2.4-2.10 and 3.1-3.8). The cookbook would benefit substantially from a shared appendix that covers the patterns once. With the per-recipe-edit posture producing diminishing returns, the trigger-idempotency appendix is the highest-leverage cookbook-wide editorial investment.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    715[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    716[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding A2 (DLQs) is operationally critical for Recipe 3.8 specifically because the system feeds care-management decisions and RPM CPT code billing documentation. The DLQ-depth alarm threshold for device-ingest, event-normalizer, and outcome-capture paths should be 1 (single-event sensitivity).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    717[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    718[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding S1 is the now-recurring PHI-minimization-inside-the-BAA pattern with the eighth distinct surface across the cookbook. Recipe 3.8's distinctive amplification is that the worklist row's narrative is itself the PHI-carrying field reaching three subscriber back ends each with its own downstream stores and logs. A cookbook-wide PHI-minimization appendix would consolidate all eight surfaces with one teaching pass.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    719[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    720[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding S2 is the seven-recipe chapter-wide subgroup-governance pattern. Recipe 3.8's subgroup taxonomy is the most comprehensive in the chapter (age bands, sex, race and ethnicity, language, insurance status, neighborhood SES, dual-eligibility status, primary diagnosis, discharge disposition; plus SDOH attributes through PRAPARE, AHC HRSN, Z-codes), and the framing-level treatment is the strongest (digital-engagement-bias amplification, three-pattern deployment-design taxonomy). The architectural backstop is the operational-completeness gap. Treat the subgroup-governance appendix as the second-highest-leverage cookbook-wide editorial investment alongside trigger-idempotency.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    721[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    722[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding S7 (patient-facing SMS/IVR vendor BAA + TCPA discipline) is the new surface this recipe introduces. Future recipes that integrate patient-facing communication channels (Chapter 4 personalization recipes, Chapter 11 conversational AI recipes) will face the same finding. Worth treating as a forward-cookbook pattern that the patient-communication appendix can consolidate.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    723[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    724[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Honest Take section is publication-ready and should be preserved verbatim. The eleven-paragraph structure (the model is the small part; patient-reported data is gold and most programs underuse it; engagement decay is one of the strongest signals; cold-start is the default state and you can't shortcut it; equity is a deployment design problem not a model problem; causal inference is the biggest research-to-production gap; biggest mistake is optimizing for the wrong metric; the political reality of fee-for-service vs value-based-care; program graduation criteria; closed-loop is not the right answer for most programs; start narrower than usual) is the kind of operations-engineer voice the cookbook is built on. The closing "lives are saved here too, just less dramatically than in Recipe 3.7" framing is the kind of moral-clarity framing that distinguishes the cookbook from documentation; it should not be shortened.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    725[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    726[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe opening Mr. Alvarez vignette is the densest post-discharge-deterioration framing in any cookbook recipe and should not be shortened. The 71-year-old, the heart-failure exacerbation with EF 30%, the daily-weights teaching, the Friday-Saturday-Sunday-Monday weight-trajectory data, the daughter taking him to the ED Monday morning, the readmission for IV diuretics and three more inpatient days at twelve thousand dollars, and the data trail showing weights went up from 198 to 199 to 201 to 204 in four days are publication-ready voice and operationally accurate.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    727[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    728[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe "Why Anomaly Detection Instead of Just Predict Readmission" subsection is the recipe's biggest pedagogical contribution and is the design distinction most published treatments blur. The framing that discharge-time risk scoring (Chapter 7 territory) and post-discharge anomaly detection are complementary should be preserved verbatim.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    729[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
